44 Sept 10 - 1857
Wilder two years old. Conference ministers here. Mr. Owen and Mr. Durbin - Latter left to go to do business with the secretary - Party at Mr Halls to night - we invited & Jenny but do not go.
Sept 27 Went to meeting this P.M. First time since July (first date.) Mr. Wilbur preached - 
Oct. 17 - Wrote to E. Putnam - sent my black bonnet to Miss Ruve to sell. Called on Mrs. Arther Ely & Miss West & Mrs. Doolittle -

Nov 13 - Went to Mr. Brooks in the eve - Home 9 1/4
Nov 14 - Letter from home -
Nov 16 - Salted meat - bought 70 lbs.
Nov. 17 - Writing to Emilia? Thinking of the gradual change that comes over us in our views of life - They grow soberer if not sadder. The joyousness in the very idea of existence that pertain to childhood and early youth is passing away and we begin to or can a little better understand the sayings of our elders

about life being 'Dear reality' or even 'a weary pilgrimage full of sorrow  But if not joyous we will try to be cheerful - perhaps we may have in the place of joy - peace -beautiful peace - the very sound of the word is soothing.  Especially if it means to us all that it may mean to the Christian.  May its holy light 'shining like the smile of God' rest ever upon thee & thine.  Anna is come over in the P.M. & I went with her to Mrs. Woolcots and Miss Priors - trimmed paper in the Eve.
Nov 18 - Mailed to E. Putnam a letter   Jenny & Wilder on to Drs.  I in P. M. to Mrs. Wilburs wash ladies securing for the home

May 12-1858-Wed,
Mother M left for Bangor with S.W.F. who came last Saturday eve. We went to Depot with them. Then Anna & I to Mrs, Runes & Morgans about Anna's new black silk   Home at 12. Care of baby in P.M. Emily carried plate to table for Mother. Isaac & Jenny in meeting in Eve.  Mr White (hypocrites.) Cleaned in front Ch. 
13. Thursday - Emily cleaned the South chamber. Jenny invited to Dr's with Celia E. to tea. She at home in Eve and I to prayer meeting.

(4 Friday) Washed windows up stairs & in the Hall - Percy went to Anne's at night to stop. Mr. White preached in Eve. Jenny & Isaac went. I called at Mr. Musseys went all over the house (below stairs)
(15 Sat) Mrs Wood & Bliss called Jenny & Isaac to M. in morn. Anna came up with them bringing mantilla skirt (grass cloth). Miss Hart came & spent day. Jenny to school house at 2 oc. I to the session room at 1/2 3. Called at Anna's, Mr Montieth, Bees? came. Jenny new bonnet

Sab, 16)  I went to morning nine o'clock meeting and in the P.M. Isaac & Jenny in Eve.  Mr Wilbur (ten talents) interesting.  Isaac read of the dealings of God with him since he thought he was a Christian 1845 - very touching indeed.  Mr. Penfield, Geo Montith, A. Bubbe Jnr - Herbert Brooks &c
Mon. 17.  29 years old - O dear me!  What have I done in all these years!  Went to morning meeting & shopping.  Mr. Mokes confession of disunion.  He led the meeting.

Tuesday 18)  Making carpet for upper hall.  Mrs. Mussey called at night. Went to meeting in Eve. Mr Wilbur preached.  
Wednesday 19)  To meeting at 8 taking Wilder.  He did well.  On carpet when I could  Mended coat &c.  Anna at night.  Hattie in P.M. She & Jenny to meeting at three.  I went to Eve meeting.
Thursday 20) Went to society at Mrs. H. Ely's.  Called at Dr's on return. Isaac went to Grafton for Dr.  took Wilder with him.

Friday - 21.  Jenny to Morning meeting & in Eve she and Isaac. I with baby.  His first tooth through to day - Isaac putting down oil cloth in Hall.  letter from Mother M. came last eve. Mailed one to Dunbarton last night.
Friday 28.  Mailed a letter to Mother M.  Libby here, all went to meeting in Eve and heard sermon read by Mr. Ely.  Letter from Mother M & one from Dunbarton with the best news.  Important conversions, young men, heads of families,

Sabbath, 30 May - I went to meeting only in P.M.  Mr White all day.  Isaac went in Eve. rainy.
Monday 31 May - clear in morn - but rained very hard before noon.  high wind blew over many trees.  large maple between here and school house 19 appl  trees of Mr. Northrup.  Rain come in to South Chamber badly.  Isaac brought home two pigs made trough &c  Percy had almost croup with Earache.

Tuesday June 1.  Woman come to wash bedding.  I with Jenny went to Eight o'clock meeting - after to Miss Reeves to see about my bonnet &c.  Helped Hattie in Arith.  Jenny and I called on Mr Mussey's - Jenny & Isaac to meeting in Eve - Made Charly's shoes.
Wednesday.  - 
Thursday - Hattie recited Latin  I went to morning meeting.  Mr Hoyle led.  Mrs Montieth & Hall spoke. Boys come to ask if ten o'c at play in Barn.  Picking clover for pigs

Friday 4  Isaac to meeting in P.M.  Isaac & I in Evening.  Mr. Hopkins preached.
Sat. 5  Jenny & I to morning meeting & to Starrs to see carpet.  Mr & Mrs Furber came while we were away.  P.P. went to get Ambro. and failed - couldn't sit still.  Isaac to young men's meeting in Eve - all to bed Early.
Sab -6 I went to meeting P.M. in Eve. monthly concert  & Isaac spoke of Europe

Monday 7 - Busy preparing Percys things  Mrs Pitts & Hattie & Libbie spent the day.  Mr & Mrs Furber left about four to take cars.  Picture of Percy & Mother - and present of one of Percy and his own mother.
Thursday 8 - Miss Crow in P.M. Mrs Mussey spent an hour or more.  Isaac hoping at Drs  Emma Come? to tea. Isaac & Jenny to meeting in Eve.

Wednesday 9 - fair - Mrs. Strong called - I went to Evening meeting
10 Thursday - Rainy in P.M.  Hattie recited Latin  I did not go to Society.  Isaac read Sermon in Eve
11. Friday - sent butter to Anna's - 1 1/2 lbs.  Rainy Isaac to morning meeting

Monday 14 - sent butter to Annas  called there to see Aunt Nancy - Mrs Hall there.
Tuesday 15 - Telegraph from Dr.  Isaac, Wilder, & I started for Grafton to get Dr. & Anna.  Met them beyond La Porte bad travelling. I went down there to tea after calling on Mrs.  Barnum? Mussey & Washburn then to meeting.

Tuesday 29 - Isaac & I went to Anna's in Eve.  Herbert B here.  Isaac to auction.  Mailed letter home.
Wednesday - 30 - Jennys package of letters by Express to Concord.  Isaac & Jenny to meeting in Eve. Jenny in P.M. also
July Friday 2 - Went to Preparatory Lecture & called at Anna's  Jenny & Isaac to meeting in Eve.
Saturday - July 3 - Comm. School Celebration at Fair ground.  rode down between Eleven & twelve

home about one on account of rain.  J. C. Grisson & J. Eills of Cleveland speakers.  Great company of people.  Fireworks, in Eve - looked from the window.  Charly & Wilder rode with us.
Sabbath - July 4 - I at home in AM.  Isaac in P.M.  Jenny in Eve.  Afternoon very interesting communion Service.  23 united with the chh by profession & four by letter - nine baptisms.

Monday July 5.  Six years since we were wed.  Hattie up to recite.  Isaac, Anna & I rode at night.
Tuesday July 6 - I went to morning meeting   Mrs Montieth & Mrs Prior prayed.  Mssrs Mussey in this P.M. Anna and I called on Mrs Nelson.  There are the two Mrs Bradfords.
Wednesday - Letter from home  Mailed answer at night

Thursday July 8 - To morning meeting   Ambrotype of Wilder.
Friday July 9 - To morning meeting - Then to get Ambrotype of baby.  Then to Anna's - Then home to find Mr & Mrs Dascome Mrs Parker and Annie Dascome.  Dr & Anna here to tea.

Saturday July 10 - Dr's mother here to dine & sup. Mrs. Mussey to supper.  Jenny to E Cranes.  Isaac to prayer meeting   Little Wilder walking on verandah with me while getting baby to sleep  Said he "there is the sky! way up there.  God lives there & good people"  Then after being still awhile.  I should'nt dare? to di? said it two or three times before I understood him. Then I asked him why.  Said because I could'nt walk there, and I should'nt be here - I should be way off.

Letter come Saturday night from Father dated Concord containing check for $20.00.
Sabbath July 11 - Rain all day.  Isaac to meeting in A.M. I read one of Bushnell's Sermons
Monday July 12 - rain - no washing mailed letter to Dunbarton to Mother M to Eliab  Sent Ambrotypes of children to Maine.

Tuesday 13 - Emily washed
Thursday - 15  I went in A.M. to society at Mrs Darlings.  Called on Mrs. Sandford. took tea at Dr DeWitts with Mr & Mrs Wicks & Rollin DeWitt
Friday 16  Letter from D.   Called on Mrs. Wood.  Libby taken with scarlitina   Mr & Mrs Weeks & Anna Called
Saturday 24 - Carpet for parlor came last night - mistake in making  I had to piece.

Sabbath 25 -
Monday 26 - went to morning meeting - bought satin to line our book case.  Anna & Dr up here at night  wrote to Dunbarton
Tuesday 27 - Mary Miller came - Emily & Isaac went after her.  Jenny to morning meeting - I put paper on my closet shelves.
Wednesday 28.  Emily left Paid her $4,50.
Friday 30 - Church meeting in P.M.

Saturday July 31 - Emma Childs & the Sanfords here to supper - Hattie DeWitt - Sophia Hart called
Sabbath - Aug 1 - I went in P.M. to meeting.  Mary went to meeting and Wedding
Monday 2 Mary came between two & three - sick  got supper and went down to Dr's to consult
Tuesday 3 - Mary went home  Paid her $1.00.

3 Jenny busy packing most of day - Herbert up here at night.
Wednesday Aug 4 - No girl  All went down to cars with Jenny and then when she was gone went to Dr's till after dinner - home about 3-  Mrs Hall called - no girl came  Mrs. Wilbur called with the boys.  I went up stairs worked some two hours cleaning away & picking up (shoes, under bed)  (blk silk apron, grass cloth shirt and towel for work basket, wash cloths) went in to Mrs Mussey's to talk of girl

Thursday Aug. 5 - Rain & lightning in the night.  Glad Jenny not on Lake.  Girl came - wanted me to wait till Monday on accout of sick Mother.  So I do   Got breakfast did up momy work, swept, filled lamps  Libby up for milk & got baby to sleep for me.  Mr. Crane put up furnace pip  I asked for Emma - No news  Herbert with book - letter from home telling Jenny to stop at W (bread sour & thrown away and gingerbread mouldy)   no girl - no Jenny

Friday 6 mailed letter to mother - Gathered the back of my white sack - went to ride about four
Saturday 7 - Washed, baked pies &c.  Read in Atlantic - "bringing our sheaves with us".  Letter from Brownville & one for Isaac from E. Crone  Anna went with us to ride   Wilder says "Aunty Jenny is gone.  When will she come home?"  I don't want her to be gone.  Wrote to Jenny in Eve.

Sabbath Aug 8 - Isaac in A.M. To meeting.  I wen ch PM. Rev Mr Moore of Greenfield O.  Text "Ye are dead in trespasses" &c 
Monday Aug 9  No girl came  no washing done - Letter form Jenny at Chatham 4 Corners all well.  Anna come up got her some squashes -  Mrs. Mussey came in.  Catharine Concklin came just bedtime.  
+Tuesday Aug 10 - Catharine Concklin began work - washed  We went to ride in P.M. baby vomited &c  Isaac cleaned

the weeds from plants in front of house - great improvement - Hattie up for milk.  Sophia Hart came up (Green corn)
Wednesday Aug 11 - Feeling bad all day.  Cold & cough &c.  Anna all day with Old Mrs. DeWitt.  Hattie up to recite. Cate ironing -   unclear & Frank Sandford called - (Fly paper)-  Letter from Samuel,  Baby sick.  Ripe tomatoes for supper. 
Thursday Aug 12 - Did not go to Society (Elyria paper - Union School) Isaac & Wilder gone all afternoon.  E. Childs to know Jenney's address. Old red bridge - 9 & 10 o'c

Friday Aug 13 - Baby feels some better. Teething  warm weather, with its little boils make him feel badly.  Letter from Jenny and mother
Saturday Aug 14 - Reading Jane Eyre - & - Baby fretful.  Wilder went down town with Cate.
Sabbath Aug 15 - Preaching A. M. & Eve.  I did not go at all
Monday Aug 16 - Wrote to mother & Jenny and Percy -

Anna came up.  Finished Jane Eyre.
Tuesday. Aug 17.  Letter went to Jenny & mother.  Not feeling well.  Rode down to Dr's - News last Eve that the first messages had passed on the Atlantic Telegraph.  Laid Aug 5, 1858.  Grand Ilumination & speeches down town in Eve - ringing bells & Herbert B. up here (ask Jenny how she opened her trunks)  also to tell me how in health our parents.
Wednesday Aug 18 - Feel weak short of breathed & bad.

Thursday - sick
Friday -         
Sabbath - 22 - begin to feel better.  Mr Wilbur left Friday for N. York - only told of it day before - D. C. White preached
Tuesday 24 - Isaac and Anna went to Commencement at Oberlin.
Wednesday 25 - Mrs Mussey - I rode down town - Got cotton cloth for skirt.  In P.M. rode to Oberlin & looked into the great crowded church

and heard Prof. Finneys speech to the Grad. Class - Nice ride;  Mrs. Peachy & twins
26 Thursday - Hattie to recite Mrs. Smith called.
Friday 27 - Rode down to Anna's an hour or two in to Mrs. Mussey's at night (We live on green corn)  Emma Crane home  McCrones bill
Saturday - 28  Letter from Jenny & mother - rainy all day  Eyes weak - Amuse myself on the floor with children - making noises on the Melodian, looking after kitchen matters.

Sabbath 29 - Mr. Fairchild of Oberlin 'Pure religion & undefeated' &c in AM - "Faith that overcometh the world' &c in P.M.  I had not been out to meeting for three weeks.
Monday 30 - rainy - carried the table up to Jenny's room from mine & brought down stand.  Isaac wrote to George in Eve (Diarrhea)
Tuesday 31 - mailed letter to George.   Anna have little while

Wednesday Sept 1 - Glorious day after so long rain it is bright again.  (ask Jenny if Mrs. Horace G in any respect resembles my old friend H. Kimball)  Herbert B. in Eve.  Mrs. Fitts & Naomi came to Dr. DeWitts - 
Thursday Sept 2  Hattie up to recite - About four went to Mr. Brooks to society - letter from mother M.  Ex wife expected to come here mid-winter
Friday 3 - Put up in cans corn & squash.  went to Lecture in P.M.  called at Anna's - saw Mrs. Harris - Mrs Fitts unwell - called at Mrs. Ponds

Saturday 4 - Isaac went to morning meeting.
Sabbath - 5.  Communion -
Monday 6 - Warm & fair  Isaac drawing stone - I wrote to Jenny.  Kate a new baby  down to Anna's after washing.  Letter mailed to Jenny.

888-246-7822
Tuesday 7 - Anna & Dr. up here - Mr. Wilbur called.  Sophia Hart came up after school.  Rollin Fitts came to live with us.
Wednesday - 8 -   Anna up - Isaac to meeting in Eve.
Thursday 9 - Isaac & I rode out to La Grange in morning - Called at Dr's.  Saw Mrs. Fitts.  Did not go to society - Called at Mr Waldos and Biggs - Kates sister came

Friday 10 - Wilder's birthday/  Evening company at Mr. Wilbur's. Letter from mother (journey to Westboro).
Saturday -11 - Made Catsup.  Went to meeting.  Kate went home.
Sabbath 12 - I went to meeting in P.M.
Monday -13.  No Kate till ten oclock at night.  I tired.  doing regular work - made some sweet pickle - & cleaned large lamp.  Mrs Mussey called, with Eugene

Tuesday 14 - Kate Washed.  I called at Anna's, Mrs. Wilburs and Mrs Topliff's.
Wednesday - 15 - Isaac, went to Sandusky to State Fair. Just wrote to Jenny. in Eve & to mother.  Looked over nasturtims & card for the cucumber pickle which do not seem to keep well.  rain in Eve.  Isaac home half past Eight
Thursday 16, mailed to Dunbarton  Went down to Anna's to supper - News of Hattie Waldo's death in Ind. at her cousins.

Friday 17 - Kate washed - in anticipation of Isaac's going East with Hattie.  Emily called.
Saturday 18 - Made gingerbread - Kate ironed & and made pie for Hattie (cream) Anna up few minutes.  I marked hand kerchiefs for Hattie & went down with them & few minutes only.  Hattie sent Wilder her doll Lettie.
Sunday 19 - Went to meeting in A. M. - tired - Hatti home at noon

Monday 20 - I went down with Isaac to Dr & took baby - Did not go to cars with Isaac & Hattie but stayed there with baby and Mrs. Fitts till the rest returned.  Then Dr. & Anna & I & baby rode out to Mrs Halls! & home the long way - fine ride.  Kate washed.  Wilder played with 'Lettie' & 'Tremont' almost all day.  Carrie Mussey come for milk for baby.  
Tuesday 21 - Dull, cloudy day.  Children both with diarrhea.  Anna came up about four.  Dr. brought tomatoes & peaches (Sophia Hart.  Anna took home three sorts pot verbenas

Wednesday  22 - Mailed to Jenny & Isaac.  Shorts at Potters   39c  Made Pickle tomatoes  Went with Anna to call Mr. H. Elys, Miss West, Mr. Slbert Bliss, Mrs. Baldwin, Mrs Lincoln, Mrs. Darling.  Starr's and bought a collar 1,12 1/2 - Children good.  Letter from George. 
Thursday, 23  Went to society at Mrs. Knowles - She to leave soon.  Mr. E. Brooks here in Eve. till most ten   fastened door for me - looked flowers at door.

Friday 24 - rainy & dull.  Leter from Isaac & Hattie last Eve.  All well & good.  Thanks for it.  Anna up little while with Libbie - canned 17 r. 1 qt.? peaches  Anna brought some to pickle.  Letter from Mother & Jenny - (Hattie gave Wilder her doll & he plays with it a good part of the time (tell Jenny) 
Saturday 25 - Fine day.  Picked Peaches.  small crock.  Tired with baby.  Kat's sister come at noon.  Baby went to her.  I went to meeting at Mrs. Cranes.  Old cow in corn & cabbages.  Rollin milked and put in road?.

Sunday 26 - 
Monday 27 - Went shopping.  Kate washed & cleaned.  Louise took care of Charly - called on Mrs. Crandall - flowers.  On Mrs. Wilbur & Peachy - Mrs. W gone  Dr. brought me home after going up to see his mother.

Tuesday 28 - Letter from Isaac & Augusta Maine - come at night - Called on Mrs Redfield and Mrs. Mussey - Anna come for dinr - Libby here  Dr's mother died about one.
Wednesday 29 Went down to Annas in A.M. & over to Mrs. Nelson. In to store for Charly flannel shirt & crash - stockings at Woolcutts.  Canned tomatoes.  Mrs. Wald called  Mrs Baldwin - stopped over an hour. Wrote to Dunbarton

Thursday 30 - Dr came over after dinner for me to go to Mr. Halls with them.  I did.  Stopped there (Dr's) on return to avoid rain. home about 5.  All night at home rain-snow-hail-rain all night.  (I took blue pill)
Friday October 1 - Went over to Anna's Early in Morn. to stay with Aunt Nancy & help Katy if I could.  The whole family to dine there after the funeral.  After they left in P.M. Anna & I called at Miss Reeves & Mrs. Knowles.

Saturday Oct 2 Isaac come in the morning from Grafton - All safe - thanks. Baggage come at night.  Letter from Mallie.  Collar & shoes.
Sabbath Oct 3 Mr. WIlbur - all day - I went all day -- Isaac in AM. but had to come out with naughty Wilder.
Monday - Oct 4.  Kate washed and ironed.
Tuesdau Oct 5 - First day pf Fair.  Kate made bread & biscuit.  I sent jar of Nasturtions.  Oberlin young men here.

Wednesday Oct 6 - I rode down to Fair grounds a little while children went with Rollin & the girls - got no unclear
Thursday Oct. 7  Rode to Fair a few moments with two children but they cried and we come home - Isaac got curtains at Mrs Knowles $1,40 per pair.  I road down to Dr's just at night - Cold & cloudy day - very windy - 
Friday Oct 8 - Anna made Jelly.
Saturday Oct 9 - I went down made grape preserves in morn 2 1/2 grapes  to meeting at Mrs. Cranes - nobody there.  Anna very busy

Sabbath Oct 10 - Isaac & I went all day to meeting.  Mr Newton of the Home Miss. soc. preached in the AM.  Mr Wilbur preached in the PM from text "Why stand ye here all the day idle" one of his best sermons - ought to be re-delivered in the AM. of next Sabbath for more to hear it.
Monday Oct 11.  Anna came up a little while in the P.M.  Her new girl come Saturday night.
Thursday, Oct. 12 - cloudy day - Emily here an hour & half. Wrote to Eliza Paddock & to Jenny.

13/mailed Jenny - 
14 Friday - Letter from Mother & George
16 Went to meeting alone in PM
17. Sabbath.  Mr Keep preached two excellent sermons "I will have mercy and not sacrifice"
18.  Herbert in eve.
19 - Letter from Jenny with Patterns -
21 Thursday - mailed letter to Mother - went to Oberlin in P.M.  Heard Mr. Finney

24.  Sabbath - Mr. W.  two excellent sermons  We heard only the A.M. Seemed to some, to contradict Mr. Keep's discourse of last Sabbath.

Monday 25 - Kate washed & cleaned windows - Went down to Miss Pomeroy about my dress.
Tuesday 26.   went down in morning and sat an hour or two sewing with Mrs. Fitts & Naomi.  Picture fr. Woolcotts
Wednesday 27 - Went down town - bought buttons and Sleeve Facing but did not use it.

went to meeting in Eve ab session rooms - and called at Drs on way home
Thursday - 28 - Rainy - did not go to Society at Mrs. Jenkins - Anna up here in morning.  Letter from George at night.  Herbert B to spend the evening.  Rollin not well. home from school
Friday - 29 - Kate cleaned in Rollin's room &c  Mrs. Carrie Mussey here in P.M. Letter from Dunbarton.  Isaac brought home table & chairs for front room.  I picked over apples in A.M.

Saturday 30 - Cloudy - Finishing green delain repairs
Sabbath 31 Oct 1 went into chh in P.M. & Evening.  Excellent Sermon.  Rollin with baby in Eve.
November 1 - Kate washed .  I at home all day - cleaned in my room, and took up the carpet in Rollins room.
Tuesay Nov 2 - rainy all day.  Wrote to Mallie a little in A long letter to George

Put down new oil cloth in dining room & put old piece in dining room closet.  Isaac to meeting in Eve.  Libby here to supper Wrote to Dunbarton
3 Wednesday - Fair - mailed to Dunbarton & Bangor.  Anna here till just three in P.M.
Thursday 4 November - At home all day - Two years since we left Dunbarton - Isaac reading loud in Eve.

Friday 5. Nov Rainy  Isaac & I rode down to church meeting.  Called at Drs on way home. Father Betts preached to the church - Duty to glorify God as members of church on Earth.  - saved by grace - grace alone.
Saturday 6 Nov. All day at home  Sewing some - reading some - letter from home, from Eliab & one to Anna from Mother M.

Sabbath Nov. 7 - Cloudy chilly day   Mr. Wilbur in morning from "And I, if I be lifted up &c  Subj: The attractions of the cross
Monday 8 rainy in AM.  Cloudy P.M.  Anna up here and the Dr. brought grape to day gathered - Wrote to Jenny & parents  Herbert here in Eve.
Tuesday 9 - Dr & Anna & Isaac & I went to Cleveland bad day   rainy - hail & wind;  but succeeded.

very well - room enough in the shops.  Bought nice furs. each cape & cuffs - &c  Home about dinner all well & right.
Wednesday 10 - I went down to Miss Reeves with my bonnet velvet, for a new sack.  She put it and flowers in $,56 cents.  Bought lining for childrens clothes for $.72 - Called at Annas.  Home about eleven.  Isaac working on wood shed.

Thursday Nov 11 - Mrs Pond called. I went to Society at Mrs Penfield's - Isaac come for me about six.  Wrote to Hattie - Talked with Mrs. Montieth
Friday Nov 12 - Sewing all day.  Isaac shirt finished, mending  Went to Bible Class in the Eve. at Mr Wilbur's.  (Annanias & Sapphira)  We called at Dr's, and did not get home till past ten.

Saturday Nov 13 - About house in AM. Cutting Charleys coat in PM. All prepared to put together.  Alone all the Eve.  Wrote to Mother M - small sheet.  Cate went to Sheffield - 
Sabbath Nov 14 - I went to meeting in AM.
Monday 15 - Kate not home till Eve   So no washing.  She went home in Eve.  Miss Pomeroy called wishing her to come to her trade at once  Isaac & I went over to Mr. Waldos.

Tuesday - 16 Nov   I went down to Anna's - saw Kats mother - she advises Kate to go to her trade.  Anna & I went to Baldwins &c - Isaac went to meeting in Eve - Kate washed
Wednesday 17 Nov   Busy all morning making cake & preparing for little girls in afternoon.  Carrie Mussey, Tilly Waldo, Libby DeWitt and Mary Hamilton - Seemed to enjoy themselves much

Thursday 18 Nov - Home all day.   Finished Charlys outside coat & cape  Isaac gone part of Eve  Kate went to tell Miss Pomeroy she would go to her trade  Expects to go Monday next
Friday - 19 Nov  Went to Bible class in Eve.  called at Drs on the way home
Saturday 20 Nov
Sabbath 21 Nov  Went to cch all day  Kate left at night.  Good!

Monday 22 Nov  Sent washing to Mrs Coughlin  Dr Dascomb come after dinner bringing Mary to spend vacation  Snowing fast when he came  Herbert here in Eve.  Father Keep Lectured but we did not go in the snow
Tuesday - 23 - Nov.   Snowing & rain all day  we reading & talking.   Eating chestnuts.  I made pumpkin pies - & rode down to get Emily for tomorrow & next day and asked Dr. & Anna & Libby to Thanksgiving dinner

Wednesday 24 Nov   dull & stormy in AM.  Emily came & attended to my treat baking and made apple pies & three pumpkin and a loaf of cake - I made some custard for supper.  Anna sent two mince pies.  I sent for Sophie Hart and Emma Crane to supper.  Sophia come about three and stayed till half past seven when she & May and Mr. Metcalf went to rehersal at the chh.   I made stuffing for the turkey and put together two plum puddings.  Tired very   Emma Crane's mother sick so she couldn't come.

Thursday 25 - Emily & I got ready for dinner.  Turkey & all   We went to meeting at Eleven  Dr, Anna, & Libby after meeting Isaac went after them because of snow.  Oyster soup, Turkey - vegetables - cranberry sauce - pudding - mince, apple pumpkin pies.
Friday 26 Nov - We went in the wagon over on the point, down by the river saw both falls - went into the stores and home again.  Anna sent for us to come there to supper.  So we did.  Jemey & Hiram Hall there, Mrs.

Ely called with Edith.  We went in to see Aunt Nancy - Mary played and we sung a great part of the Eve.  Mixed bread after  came home 
Saturday 27 Nov - Snowy - Carrie Mussey called   Mary reading Shirley - & playing melodian - I about housework most all day
Sabbath 28 - I did not go in morning to meeting.   Snowed all night - four or five inches of snow.  Mary went all day.  I went in PM. Dr. Aikis? of Cleveland preached  Pres. Board of Pub  in P.M.

Monday 29 Nov   Housework in AM.  Mary, Anna & I went into school in PM. and Mary & I called on Mrs. Barnum & at Mr. Musseys    
Tuesday 30 Nov Clear, cold - Thowing? some   Isaac took sleigh and started for Oberlin to take Mary home about nine in the morning.  WIlder went too - I sent washing to Mrs Caughlin again  Louise home most of the day to help her mother

Isaac came about two oclock. very bad traveling indeed.  wrote long letter to Dunbarton.  I have weeks since I mailed the last
Wednesday Dec 1  Busy in Kitchen in morn.  Mrs. Mussey came about Eleven  I dressed and started after she left - in a hurry for meeting - But was so late I thought I would not go in.  Called on Mrs Baldwin went and waited sometime for Anna.  finally started, and met Isaac went to Baldwin's with him & found Anna  bought 8 yds of canton flannel. went home

with Anna to rest a little - called on Mrs Potter, Mrs Gates, Miss Brooks & Mrs Monteith   made arrangements for Serving Soc. nex week.  Home about four.  got Supper  Isaac went to meeting
Thursday 2 Dec - Worked about house all day cleaned the china closet & the kitchen cupboard & unclear up stains & made bed in front room  Louise took Charly out to ride - Found her mother sick - wants her to come home tomorrow  Letter from George

Friday 3 Dec - Took down books in the book case & dusted & put back  Louise went home at twelve to stay.  Libby here to Lunch.  Isaac went to meeting at two.  I stayed with the babies.  Charly sore finger  Isaac & I both at home in Eve.  Rollin at Mr White.
Saturday 4 Dec - In kitchen about all day  Cooked goose  made pumpkin pies of sweet pumpkin from Mr Waldo's.  Herbert here in Eve

Sabbath Dec 5.  No girl so I went out only in the P.M. while Rollin stayed with Charly & Wilder.
Monday Dec 6  Last week cloths came home - in part.  Shall have no washing done this week.  In kitchen most of day   Anna up a little while - Isaac brought home dozen white coffee cups & saucers & dozen blue plates.

Tuesday, Dec. 7 - Sweeping upstairs, cleaning in kitchen.  Remainder of clothes came.  Engaged Louise? to come tomorrow & next day.  Emily came to see if I wanted her.  told her yes. Anna & Dr up at night and we all went to the young people's meeting - It was good & interesting -
Wednesday Dec 8 - Some did not come for some reason.  Anna come to help me make cake, Emily come.  made out my bread  washed oil cloth & ktichen & pantry floor &c &c &c

Anna sent for Libby to see to the children.  She helped make three loaves cake.  I made three after she left.  After Emily went away I had the to?p..s? to take up & peel  Isaac did this for me.  I strained the apple sauce & mixed my sponge for biscuits tomorrow.  Then made button holes and sewed on buttons to Charlys new dress.  Anna took home the skirt to finish for me.  Tired-

Thursday Dec 9 - Emily came between nine & ten.  Louise come too.  Dusted rooms & brushed when needed.  had biscuits made out to rise.  I sat down to finish baby's & dress.  got it done.   cut up meat & cheese with Emily.  She attended to bread baking with good success.  I dressed and was ready for the ladies just as the first one come  Mrs. Topliff  Thirteen here inside   Libby home sick & some did not know about it.  Mrs Mussey in - pleasant time -

Friday Dec 10 - Louise come - I mended all day.  Louise cared for baby & hemmed two towels.  Anna come up a few moments.  She was calling & shopping.  Isaac & I went to Bible Class in Eve.  I called at Mr. Baldwin's on way - Called at Dr's coming home.
Saturday Dec 11 - Decided to send for Katy as Betty had not heard from her cousin  so Isaac went to Avon for her  came about three.  Then Bettys cousin came about Dark, too.

So I have them both.  feel a little sorry to have two girls just now - shouldnt have gone for Katy had we known the other was coming.  Isaac gone in Eve - about young men's Christian Ass.
Sabbath Dec 12 - Girls do very well. Charly seems to go very Easily to Zillah and her ways seem to suit him - I went to meeting in the Morning & left him with her.
Monday - 13 - Girls washing - Bad day to dry cloths - Herbert here Monday Eve

Tuesday 14 Dec - Mr. Clark came to help Isaac kill the pigs - got it done  Clothes did not get dry  no ironing except calico's dryed in house  Isaac to meeting in the Eve
Wednesay 15 Dec - Rainy - Took in the clothes put in tubs.  Did not go to meeting.  tried out Sands?
Thursday 16 - Fair I went down to Anna Early in Morning to ask about

making sausage meat.  Girls got the clothes out.  Anna & I went in the P.M. to Mrs Darlings, Wilburs Rollin DeWitts & Mrs Doolittle, & I to Mrs Coles.  Bought buttons for my calico dress.  Home by supper time (Mrs A Starr clalled ) (Made sausage before going)
Friday17  Made head cheese  Girls ironing - Sweeping &c   Some expect Eliab tomorrow Sewing on my dress in P.M.  Went over to Mrs. Musseys by request to the Baptist  sewing Soc, 35 ?ydent? & to Bible Class in Eve.

Saturday 18 Dec - Out in Kitchen all AM. Finishing up with the pigs - helping Katy with Coffee Cakes &c   Sophia Hart here in P.M  also Mrs. Doolitle & Miss Kemp.  Isaac got dispatch from Eliab to meet him at Grafton to night - sat down to supper & bell rung and Eliab had come - Walked from Grafton.  And Mother & Irving at Brigehampton. Doleful.  Little Irving not well - sorry, sorry.  Anna come up & Dr come

Sabbath 19 Dec  Cloudy & rainy - All went to Meeting in AM I went in P.M.  Isaac to S. S. Eliab at home.  Isaac & E to meeting to Dr's in eve. wrote cable home & to George
Monday 20 Dec  Washing but not put out clothes - rainy most all day Isaac & Wilder & I with Eliab about all day at Drs   Home about 5 and Isaac, much against his will & judgement, went to take Eliab to Grafton.

Anna & I in morning went out and bought books &c to send to Irving and Lucy.  I got Longfellows Courtship of Miles Standish & a cloth book for Wilder & Charlie.  I writing in Eve.  Isaac about ten.
Tuesday 21 Dec.  Mrs. Austin & Miss Long called  I at home all day. Isaac down to Dr's &c and meeting in Eve. Letter from Maria to Eliab.  Little Lucy's picture.
Wednesday 22 Dec - Pleasant - Put cloths out  & dried them.  Anna & Dr up here all night.  We all went together to meeting.

Thursday 23 Dec.  Pleasant day - I went at 10 to go with Anna to Miss Reeves about velvet bonnet.  Isaac carried me down & took boys and basket for Soc. to Mrs. Smiths.  I came home about noon.  Went to Soc about four - twelve ladies in all - pleasant time.  Mrs. Ely quite attentive &c - asked about furs   Isaac come for me at seven 
Friday 24 Dec.  At home all day - Isaac went in morning for Wilbur boys.  They stayed all day.  Isaac took them home about five. Sew.Mac.came

Made Wilder & Libbie Port folios in Eve.  Letter from Mary Thurston at night.
Saturday 25 - Dec.  Pleasant.  Katy to meeting at eight till ten.  Wilder happy enough with his candy & Portfolio & Gingerbread man, woman, rat - that Katie made.  Libby came & brought him a book & some pictures pasted into a book that pleased him very much indeed.  She brought Charlie a book of pictures too.  Issac with Sew. Mac. all day  I went at three and we both dined there.  Isaac to young Mens Chris. Ass. first meeting in Eve   I writing home in Eve - Herbert

Sabbath 26 Dec- I went to meeting in AM. came home with Wilder in the rain. Isaac to S.S. in PM. Writing & reading in Eve.
Monday 27 Dec -Mailed letters to Mother M & to Dunbarton.  Letters from Jenny & mother at night.  Sewing all day.  Mended Isaac's velvet vest & made shoes for charley &c.  Down to Anna's all the Eve.  Isaac sewing.  I tried a little.  Invitation to Dr Strongs tomorrow Evening at Seven o'clock.

Tuesday 28 Dec - Anna here a little while.  We called there in Eve on way to Dr Strong's.  Isaac went to meeting first.  About 150 invations and 45 not present  Pleasant time.
Wednesday 29 Dec. Rainy - Did not go to evening meeting. 
Thursday 30 Dec   Anna up here.  Cutting out work.  Sunrises? Called at Mrs Snows & Olmstd.

Friday 31 Dec.  I went to Anna's to settle meeting turn with Mrs. Fitts. Went to meeting at two.  Full meeting.  Emma Crane here to supper.  We went at seven to Mr WIliburns   Above 30.  Saw Christmas presents to Mr & Mrs WIlburn & Elegant Bible from Cincinnati.
Saturday 1 Jan.  Dr up here about noon for the walk  Wilder went to Emily's with Katy.

Sabbath Jan 2 - I went all day.  Mr Wilbur Communion in P.M.   Mrs Nelson Smiths children baptised.
Monday Jan 3  Went to Mrs. Montieth & Mr Wilburs - called to ask Miss Kemp to sit up with Mrs Fitts.  Over to Anna's till Isaac came from Meeting.  Met Mrs Ely in street.  She asks Isaac & I to take her there tomorrow Eve

Tuesday Jan 4 - Sewing AM.  About four went down to Annas with sewing - sat with Mrs Fitts while they were at supper.  Isaac came about five - We all went to Mr Ely's - pleasant time.  Miss Goodwin & Mrs. Taylor of Cleveland Mrs. Temples.  Mrs Seagrath of Mrs. Judge Ely's sister.  Mrs. Taylor, Mrs Temples sister.
Wednesday Jan 5. Preparing work in morning   About three down to Anna's   Called Mrs. Pond  Miss Burrile Mrs. Prior  Miss B's gone  Mrs. P, sick.  Mrs. Wooster set up Mrs Fitts

Thursday Jan 6 - Went down to Anna's to meet Mr. Bullock & attend to sewing machine & home about half past one.  Zillah sat up with Mrs. Fitts.  Herbert Brooks here at night Took tea.  Rainy, Evening.
Friday Jan 7 - Home all day - grew cold at night.  Letter from Hattie
Saturday Jan 8  Cold morning Down to zero.  Isaac gone all day   Eve to Y. M. C. A.  I sewing.

Sabbath Jan 9 - I went to meeting all day.  Did not thaw at all.  Wore socks.   Mr. Wilbur preached   Evening reading "Power of Prayer".
Monday Jan 10  - 6º below Zero - grew warmer towards night. Anna up here in morning. I went down there to sew in P.M.  succeeded better than before.  Letter from Dunbarton at night. Jenny, father, & mother.  Isaac gone in Eve.  Mr & Mrs. Waldo here

Tuesday Jan 11 -  Isaac went down town for eggs, pudding dish, platter &c.  Went for Mrs Montieth about 11.  Anna came about 12.  Dr. soon after - Dinner 1/2 past one - Pleasant time - Isaac took Mrs M. home about four - Isaac lame - rhumatism - Did not go to meeting in Eve.
Wednesday Jan 12   I sewed in AM. Called at Mr Crandalls in P.M. at Woocutts for thimble, Wilder stockings, and at Potter's for yarn, insertion pins - Then to Anna's - sat with Aunt Nancy. Home to tea

Thursday Jan 13 - Called at Anna's and went to Mrs. Rood to sew - carrying cake & biscuit & cheese for tea  Pleasant company - home in slight rain about six & a half oclock.  About seven Mr. W. Nevins came to spend evening - talking, ate apples &c
Friday Jan 14 - Preparing sewing, writing to Albina & Almeda  filing letters &c in AM.  Isaac &  I down to Drs about two.  Isaac Sewell, I sat with Aunt Nancy while they dined &c.  Herbert here in Eve.  Letter from George.  (Jenny to be married next Sept.)  Sheffield boy died of scarlet fever.
Saturday Jan 15  - Sewing all day & finished one pr chemises.  Anna & Dr here an hour at night.  Isaac gone P.M. & Eve - Y.M.C.A.

Sabbath Jan 16  Went to meeting all day  Rev Mr Clark agent of ABCFM in AM  Mr WIlbur on Temperance in P.M.
Monday Jan 17 - Snowy  Wrote to Jenny & mother & father and to Mr D Thurston  - sewed home - went down to Dr's in Eve.  Called Dr Strongs - Home read Atlantic till Eleven.
Tuesday Jan 18 - Started at Eleven with Wilder  Called at Mrs. Sandfords & Cranes.  Then to Anna's - sewed till thru - went with her to call on Mrs Cogswell, Austin, McLong, P. Bliss.  Home to supper.  With Isaac to Mr. Elys & T. P. Prayer Meeting

Wednesday Jan 19  -  Cutting out Shirts. & finishing chemise - Mrs Mussey here in P.M.  I went to meeting in Eve.  Called at Dr's coming home.  Mrs Waldo sat up with Mrs. Fitts
Thursday Jan 20 - Went down about three to Drs and Sewed till half past four then went to Society at Mrs Woosters - Home in great rain with lantern & umbrella.
Friday Jan 21 - (Letter from Dunbarton)  Went to Dr's about ten - sewed till about three - Ama walked home with me - & down in grove  Put Bosoms in shirts . Mrs Riggs & baby came in - Isaac Drs all eve till 10 1/2 oc

Saturday Jan 22 - Snowy & cold.  FInished the pair of shirts I began Thursday.  Wrote to George & to Dunbarton in Eve.  Isaac gone to Ass. rooms
Sabbath Jan 23 - I went all day to chh.  Some tired.  Girls went in Eve  I  heard Anna's class in SS because she had swelled face & ear.

Monday_Jan 24 - cold  Taking care of chldren  Isaac drawing wood.  & is YMCA in Eve.  Herbert here in Eve till half past ten  -
Tuesday Jan 25 - Went down to see Anna in P.M.   Mrs. Finn there - Mr & Mrs Hall   Sewed a little on Charley's apron.
Wednesday Jan 26 - Cut out nightgowns &c.  Went to Meeting in Eve.  Called at Mr Crandall's - Left 'Courtship of Miles Standish".  Went to meeting then in Reading Room of YMCA  Then to see Anna till 1/2 past nine

Thursday Jan 27  Frances Sanford called with tickets for Festival.  We took two.  I did not go to Society - at Mrs P. Bliss
Friday Jan 28 - Went down to Anna's in P.M. with my sewing.  Sat with Mrs. Fitts.  Presentation to the school Festival.  A crowded house.  Home before eleven
Saturday 29  Sewed &c till half past two - went down to Anna's and read to her and Libbie.

Sabbath Jan 30--  I went to meeting in AM & eve.  Zillah and Katy in P.M.  I heard Anna's class
Monday Jan 31--  Mended Isaac's pants, coat &c took care of children -- regulated drawers, wrote to parents & Jenny-- went to lecture in Eve.  George Summer--Old Europe & Young America  Especially as regards education (facilities for education) Ireland 5000 National Schools-- 540,000 pupils 800,000 inhabitants-- Greece -  4 Universities in only 20 years-  France & Holland

Tuesday, Feb 1,  1859--
Isaac left about eleven  Rollin took him to Oberlin -- take cars there for Toledo  Thence to Springfield Ills & to Du Quoin-- Know not how long he may be away-- I with Wilder called at Mr Olmstead's, Mr Wilburs and at Annas- Did not go to Mrs Doolittle's party- Wrote in Eve to Mother M. Mailed letter to Dunbarton in morn.  Mr & Mrs Harris at Anna's-

Wednesday, Feb 2- Rainy- & Snowy all day- Libbie came up and spent the day-  Anna up in P.M.  Mrs Wilbur had been there- Said out of the 200 invitation to Mrs D's party, were only 15 regrets-- had dancing.. Mary Long & Nettie Wheeler danced-- At night came letter from Dunbarton one from Isaac mailed at Toledo and a Bank affair wh. I must take to the Dr to get explained- Do not feel very well - sick at stomach &c.

Thursday Feb 3- Snowy- I went down to Dr's in morning with Isaacs letter &c - Bank circular to show to Dr. thought it amounted to nothing-- Anna & I went into store- Miss Pomeroys, Mr- Wilburs- I home about twelve, Calling at Mr Ponds- Cut out chemise for Missionary box & sewed some on it in P.M.  Rollin did not go to meeting in Eve.  Stayed with his mother all night  Wrote to Isaac  Did not go to Society at A.A. Bliss.

Friday Feb 4- Snowy- Finished & mailed letter to Isaac  Rollin home to do chores-- Uncle Harris came for Eunice? as we were at breakfast again  His mother was dead before they got back there.  Rollin got gallon coal oil & paid for qt. $1.56: I went down to meeting - called at Anna's going & returning-- called at Mrs Doolittle excused over non-attendance at the party-- went to stores- Bought Ladies cloth for basque- & norun? for skirt- Good meeting -  (Judgment put off to the End of the world because the results of a persons life are not till then known.

Saturday Feb 5--  Slight snow all day-  Rollin down to Dr most of day home to do chores- cut a little wood-  I sewing on garment- for the Miss. Box- Herbert here- Told me of the Thursday evening meeting (Took home "Steam Engine")
Sabbath Feb 6- I went to meeting in AM & evening.  Zilliah in P.M.  Katy went home with Emilie's husband-- back about half past eight- Wrote to Isaac in Eve. Harvey? here

Monday Feb 7-  Fine day  Zero in morn at seven o'clock-  grew warmer   Miss Crow here- fitted my cloth basque & calico wrapper  Sent Independent to Herbert to take to reading room- Letter came from Isaac mailed Springfield last Thursday-
Tuesday Feb 8- (wrote home in eve)  Beautiful day- I went down to Dr's about half past nine & did what I could to help-- made Libbie a shade, dusted &c - Funeral at one.  I stayed with Libbie regulated rooms-- home about three - Called on Mrs. Simons-

Wednesday Feb 9- Snowy in morning- grew cold towards noon & stopped snowing-- Rollin went to Mr Halls-- Anna too with all the sisters of the Dr- I sewed on calico dress-- Went to prayer meeting and after to the Lecture F. B. Walker - A Poesn? - Narrative of the Life of a Lady of Fashion- Letters from Mother M & from Jenny & mother-

Thursday Feb 10-- 
Sewing in A.M. After dinner went down with Wilder & called at Anna's (Mrs Wilbur first)  Met Mrs Doolittle & her mother coming up here-  Waited for Anna to go to Society at Mrs Washburns thirty four there-- Mrs Ely said her husband liked Mr Metcalfs class in SS very much Mrs. Bliss spoke of the Social companions on Friday Eve--

Friday Feb 11 - Went and called for Anna & went to Starrs and got binding for basque  &c  Yarn at Wolcutts & told him about our clock.  Went in to Mrs. Musseys coming home.  We are both invited to Mrs. Ponds to tea to night.  I sewed till about three then went there - ten ladies beside me. Mr Strong & Madam Strong, Mrs & Madm Mussey Mr & Mrs Brooks, Mrs Wooster, Mrs C. Doolittle, Miss Ferrell, Mrs Wilbur & Mrs Peachy invited but did not come.  Two letters from Isaac   Went over to Dr Griswolds in Eve

Saturday Feb 12 - Snowing - Rollin down town to get measured for coat.  Mailed letter to Isaac - Mr Crane came to see to the pump - said it must be frozen somewhere.  Left Rollin to try to thaw it out.  Miss Trescott spent the P.M.  Herbert in the Evening.
Sabbath Feb 13 - Snowy.  I went to meeting in AM  Zillah & Katy in the P.M.  I went in Eve to S.S. concert - very good meeting.  Mr WIlbur about coming to Christ.  Mr Root - Mr Brooks - Little girl prayed to have her blue ticket changed to a pink one so she might have a book.  Mr Ely servants "Susies'  Wrote letter to Isaac to Mother & Jenny..

Monday - Feb 14 - Fair in AM.  Cloudy in PM.  Anna up here in A.M.  I made a cake after dinner.  Wrote to Isaac & finished up letter to Dunbarton.  Sent both to office .
Tuesday, Feb. 15.  Invited to Mr. Vincents this Eve at  Seven o'clock.  Shall not go.  Mrs H. E. Mussey came over & stayed an hour.  I read some in Friends & Lorter?.  Sewed on my basque.  Letter at night from Isaac saying he might be home this week.

Wednesday Feb. 15 - Sewing in AM. Anna & Libbie here after dinner.  I went home with them and stayed to the evening meeting & Lecture - Letter from Emily Putnam.
Thursday Feb 17 - rainy most of day - I started about half past three, called at Anna's and took her work &c to Society at Mrs Vincents  Went to prayer meeting in the Eve.  Letter from Isaac - of the fourteenth - Home Saturday

Friday Feb 18 - Went to ask Mr & Mrs. Mussey and Mrs Simons to tea.  Sent Rollin to Anna, Mrs. Olmstead, Mrs. Waldo & Pond - made loaf of cake. & attended to floating island &c.  Mr & Mrs Brooks came about two oclock  Isaac came giving me a delightful surprise  Had a pleasant company thirteen at table. Letter from Dunbarton
Saturday Feb 19  -  At home all day - cutting out skirts  Isaac went to Oberlin to get his baggage - very bad travelling.  We both went down to Dr's in Eve.

Sabbath Feb. 20 - I went with Wilder & Rollin to meeting in AM.  Isaac went in P.M. Reading Primitive Piety Revived - 
Monday Feb 21  Cutting out work all AM  Anna came up after dinner & wanted me to call & shop with her. Called on Mrs Vincent & Darling and Mrs Prior and went to the store. Got Charley aprons &c  Herbert here in Eve.
Tuesday. Feb 22  Pleasant  I wrote to Dunbarton & to E Putnam.

Wednesday Feb. 23 - Went down to Annas in P.M. Called on Mrs. Finn. Sewed on machine.  Isaac came down to supper.  We all went to meeting & to Lecture.  Mr. Fairchild of Oberlin. Excellent subject "Hidden Power"  - rainy all the Eve.
Thursday Feb 24 -  Home all day.  Went to meeting in Eve. Prayer meeting for Colleges &c and young people's meeting there often.
Friday Feb 25 - Mr & Mrs WIlbur and Dr & Anna here to dine  I invited to Mrs Musseys to tea & went

Sataurday Feb 26 - Fair - Home.  Reading Atlantic & knitting for Charlie.
Sabbath Feb 27 - Fair  I went to meeting in the A.M. and Eve.  Ridgeville minister exchanged with Mr WIlbur - "Stand fast therefore in the liberty wherewith Christ hath made you free"  &c.
Monday Feb 28 - Took care of children in AM - Went down to Anna's about 1/2 past three and we called at Mrs H. Beebee Mrs. Hall, Mrs Barnum & Mrs Montieth & teachers

Wrote to George, Isaac gone all the eve - Rollin stayed at home from a party at the Gates because he was so advised.
Tuesday, March 1 - Went into school with Anna and down to Mrs. Elys, Howards A. Beebee, and on the way home called at Mr Faxon? - Went in Eve to Hutchinsons concert with Luca Brothers - very good indeed  Very tired -
Wednesday March 2  - Head ache - Went to meetng and Lecture by Dr Newberry in Eve.  On Colorado River - good -

As Isaac says about Charlie Wilder and Charles where or'ed they and what do not they do?  Charles lumbers about the house with the agility of a hippopotamus, he climbs up by chains &c.  climbs down onto the door step to go out doors and climbs up one step to go up stairs and then sets down to rest and falls off

Do we not wish to grow in a religious aspect? To feel more and more acquainted with God & Christ   We are not satisfied with out intellectural attainments.  we wish to grow constantly in this regard.  How much more shd we wish to grow spiritually to be humbler & more Christlike in our lives Everyday.
I was just thinking of a sentence I read somewhere.  When we sit by ourselves, thinking, in our own room, we fancy we could Even be martyr but we go out to our daily duties in our family and find we cannot bear even an impatient word

buy music - 
Jeny write me about [Mary?]] AM.  Wilder says come Charly come Let's go like sixty.  Up stairs cleaning front chamber he said "Those men shouldn't do so cous? this is Percy's room]& grandmothers room.  They shouldn't do so".  Waked up crying in night, saying "Mama hers put my dear little brother out doors - he is dead & I can't see him any more".  Dreaming, doubtless.  "Does God see me now" yes. "Is he peeking out of Heaven to see me now?  A new application of the word, I thought
